Eid-ul-Adha: The Festival of Sacrifice
Eid-ul-Azha: Azmat-e-Ibrahim (A.S) ki Mukammal Tareekh
1. Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S) ka Imtehan
Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S) jinhein "Khalil-ullah" (Allah ka dost) kaha jata hai, unki puri zindagi imtehanon se bhari thi. Allah Taâ€™ala ne unhein budhapa mein ek beta ata farmaya, jinka naam Hazrat Ismail (A.S) tha. Jab beta thoda bada hua (daudne dhoopne ki umar ko pahuncha), to Allah ne Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S) ko khwab mein dikhaya ke wo apne bete ko zabeh (qurban) kar rahe hain.

Ambiya (A.S) ka khwab "Wahi" hota hai, isliye unhone ise Allah ka hukum samjha.

2. Baap-Bete ka Be-misal Jazba
Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S) ne apne bete se poocha, "Beta, main ne khwab mein dekha hai ke main tumhein zabeh kar raha hoon, tumhari kya raye hai?"

Hazrat Ismail (A.S) ne wo tareekhi jawab diya jo qayamat tak ke liye misal ban gaya:

"Aye mere baap! Aap wahi kijiye jiska aapko hukum diya gaya hai, InshaAllah aap mujhe sabr karne walon mein payenge."

Ye sirf ek bete ka jawab nahi tha, balki Allah ki rida (raza) mein khud ko fana karne ka ailaan tha.

3. Mina ka Maidan aur Mojza
Dono baap-bete Mina ke maidan ki taraf nikal pade. Raste mein Shaitan ne teen jagah par Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S) ko behkane ki koshish ki taake wo bete ki mohabbat mein qurbani se peeche hat jayen, lekin Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S) ne har baar usay kankariyan maarin (jiski yaad mein aaj bhi Haji "Rami" karte hain).

Jab Hazrat Ibrahim (A.S) ne apne bete ko peshani ke bal litaya aur apni aankhon par patti bandh kar churi chalayi, to Allah ki qudrat se churi ne asar nahi kiya. Allah ko unka ye jazba-e-sadiq itna pasand aaya ke Hazrat Ismail (A.S) ki jagah jannat se ek "Dumba" bhej diya gaya jo qurban ho gaya.

4. Hajj aur Qurbani ka Rishta
Eid-ul-Azha ka taluq Hajj se bhi bohot gehra hai. 10 Zil-Hajj ko puri duniya se aaye hue Haji bhi isi sunnat ki yaad mein qurbani karte hain. Ye din musalmanon ki ittehad (unity) aur ek rang hone ki nishani hai.

5. Qurbani ke Aham Maqasid (Reasons)
Sunnat-e-Ibrahimi ki Pairwi: Hum har saal janwar qurban karke ye wada karte hain ke agar Allah ke liye apni jaan ya aulaad ki qurbani deni padi, to hum peeche nahi hatenge.

Nafs ki Qurbani: Janwar par churi chalane ka matlab hai apne andar ki buraiyon, lalach, aur garoor ko khatam karna.

Ghareebon ki Imdad: Is din gosht ke 3 hisse karne ka hukum hai:

Ek hissa Ghareebon aur Miskeenon ke liye (taake wo bhi saal mein kam az kam ek baar accha khana kha saken).

Ek hissa Rishtedaros aur Doston ke liye (muhabbat badhane ke liye).

Ek hissa Apne ghar ke liye.